      "name": "K8s - PodRestarts Detected",
      "description": "The alert is activated when a pod restarts more than a predefined threshold (1) within a specified time window (e.g., 10 minutes), signaling instability in the pod's operation.\n\nAction: Investigate the pod's logs and events to identify the root cause of the restarts. Common causes include:\n      - Application crashes or unhandled exceptions\n      - Misconfigured resource requests/limits leading to insufficient resources\n      - Failing health checks (liveness/readiness probes)\n      - Issues with environment variables or secrets\n    Resolve the issue by addressing the application bugs, adjusting resource limits, optimizing health checks, or reviewing other configuration issues that might be causing instability.",
      "enabled": false,
      "priority": "ALERT_DEF_PRIORITY_P3",
      "type": "ALERT_DEF_TYPE_METRIC_THRESHOLD",
      "groupByKeys": [
